Phase 2 (Analysis & Mapping) involved analyzing all files and mapping them to proper categories using the standardized naming convention: YYYY-MM-DD - Client Name - Category - Originator - Description. Phase 3 (Quality Review) achieved a 0.0% error rate, with 0 errors across 28 case files, and the files were approved for execution. Phase 4 (Execution) completed 23 file operations: 21 move operations (comprising 16 PDF+MD pairs and 5 non-PDF files) and 2 duplicate deletions, with zero execution errors. Phase 5 (Verification) ensured all files were properly organized into the eight-bucket structure.

Final File Distribution included the following: Client — 7 files (fee agreement, intake form, HIPAA authorization); Insurance — 15 files (organized by BI/PIP with Direct Auto Insurance subfolders); Investigation — 3 files (LMPD traffic collision report); Medical Records — 18 files (organized by provider: Starlite Chiropractic, UofL Health - Mary & Elizabeth Hospital); Negotiation Settlement — 3 files (settlement demand package and draft); and Case Information — 12 files (JSON databases).
